  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6756 sitting above the GEX flip (6715) but caught between massive negative gamma at 6750 (-10B) and positive gamma at 6775 (+6B), dealers are currently buying this move higher as they're short gamma. The recent regime flip into BREAKOUT mode with -9.8B total GEX means dealers will amplify moves - buying rallies toward 6775 resistance and aggressively selling any dip back toward the 6745-6750 negative gamma cluster. Watch 6775 as the critical level where dealer selling should kick in hard, while any break below 6750 triggers accelerated dealer buying that could spark a sharp bounce.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect volatile swings between 6750 and 6775 with dealers pushing price to extremes rather than providing stability.",
